    "ts": "2026-03-12T11:17:00+00:00",
    "headline": "Atlassian to Cut 10% of Jobs Citing AI. How Its CEO Tried a Human Touch for the Layoffs.",
    "summary": "Atlassian is cutting around 10% of its workforce as it embraces the future of artificial intelligence—but it tried to adopt more of the human touch with its approach.  The workflow software company said it will reduce its head count by around 1,600, in a bid to rebalance the company in the AI era.  “Decisions require heart (humanity, empathy, passion,) and balance (pragmatism, trade-off, decisiveness,” CEO Mike Cannon-Brookes wrote.",
